# {{ project_name }} — Claude Code project rules

See @AGENTS.md for project-wide rules.

## Claude-specific supplements

- Use `just verify` (exit 0 = done) before claiming any task complete. This is the only
  ground truth — do not substitute test output or lint output alone.
- Hooks land in Phase 3: `PostToolUse` runs lint + typecheck; `Stop` runs `just verify --quick`.
  Override with `VERIFY_KIT_SKIP=1` when you need to stage work-in-progress.
- Skills land in Phase 3 under `.claude/skills/verify-kit-{verify,debug,eval}/`.
- Use `bd` (beads) for any multi-step task tracking — never inline TODO files or TodoWrite.
- Never read `.env`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, or credential files. `.env.example` is safe to read.
- Never `git add .` — always stage files individually by name.

## verify-kit Conventions

The canonical agent rules for this project live in [AGENTS.md](./AGENTS.md). The
notes below are Claude-Code-specific additions.

- Before declaring "done", `just verify --quick` MUST exit 0. The Stop hook in
  `.claude/hooks/stop.sh` enforces this.
- Edit/Write tool calls trigger `.claude/hooks/post-tool-use.sh` which runs
  `just lint && just typecheck`. Fix issues before continuing.
- Set `VERIFY_KIT_SKIP=1` to bypass the Stop hook for emergency work; record
  the reason in the commit message.
- MCP tools (`verify`, `list_checks`, `describe`, `trace_last`, ...) are available
  when the `verify-kit` MCP server is registered in `.claude/settings.json`'s
  `mcpServers` block (see `.claude/settings.json.example`).
